# рЯЪА DAY 4 вАФ Objects + `type` vs `interface` (рЯФ• VERY IMPORTANT)

---

# рЯІ† 1. Why We Need Object Types

In JS:

```js
const user = {
  name: "Ayush",
  age: 21
};
```

рЯСЙ No safety. You can mess it up anytime.

---

## вЬЕ In TypeScript:

```ts
const user: { name: string; age: number } = {
  name: "Ayush",
  age: 21
};
```

рЯСЙ Now TypeScript protects you.

---

# рЯІ† 2. Cleaner Way вАФ Type Alias

```ts
type User = {
  name: string;
  age: number;
};
```

Use it:

```ts
const user: User = {
  name: "Ayush",
  age: 21
};
```

---

# рЯІ† 3. Interface (Same PurposeвА¶ but different behavior)

```ts
interface User {
  name: string;
  age: number;
}
```

Use it the same way:

```ts
const user: User = {
  name: "Ayush",
  age: 21
};
```

---

# вЪФпЄП 4. `type` vs `interface` (INTERVIEW FAVORITE рЯФ•)

## рЯЯҐ Similarities:

* Both define object shapes
* Both are used everywhere

---

## рЯФі Differences:

### 1. Extension

рЯСЙ Interface:

```ts
interface User {
  name: string;
}

interface Admin extends User {
  role: string;
}
```

рЯСЙ Type:

```ts
type User = {
  name: string;
};

type Admin = User & {
  role: string;
};
```

---

### 2. Flexibility

рЯСЙ Type can do more:

```ts
type Status = "success" | "error"; // union
```

рЯСЙ Interface cannot do this вЭМ

---

### 3. Declaration Merging (рЯФ• tricky concept)

```ts
interface User {
  name: string;
}

interface User {
  age: number;
}
```

рЯСЙ Automatically becomes:

```ts
{
  name: string;
  age: number;
}
```

рЯСЙ Type DOES NOT allow this вЭМ

---

# рЯІ† 5. When to Use What (IMPORTANT)

рЯСЙ My recommendation (and industry trend):

* Use `interface` вЖТ for objects (especially React props)
* Use `type` вЖТ for everything else (unions, complex types)

---

## рЯФ• Interview Answer (MEMORIZE THIS)

> вАЬI prefer `interface` for object structures due to extendability and readability, and `type` when I need unions or advanced compositions.вАЭ

---

# рЯІ† 6. Optional Properties

```ts
type User = {
  name: string;
  age?: number;
};
```

рЯСЙ `age` is optional

---

# рЯІ† 7. Readonly Properties

```ts
type User = {
  readonly id: number;
  name: string;
};
```

```ts
user.id = 5; // вЭМ Error
```

---

# рЯІ† 8. Nested Objects (REAL WORLD)

```ts
type User = {
  name: string;
  address: {
    city: string;
    pincode: number;
  };
};
```

---

# рЯІ† 9. Using in Functions

```ts
type User = {
  name: string;
  age: number;
};

function greet(user: User): string {
  return `Hello ${user.name}`;
}
```

---

